本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:李宗原研究生(外文):Tsung-Yuan Lee論文名稱:美國國防部對臺海安全之評估，2001-2008論文名稱(外文):An Evaluation on the Cross-strait Security as Performed by U.S. Department of Defense, 2001-2008指導教授:林正義學位類別:碩士校院名稱:東吳大學系所名稱:政治學系學門:社會及行為科學學門學類:政治學類論文出版年:2008畢業學年度:96語文別:中文論文頁數:199中文關鍵詞:臺海安全、台灣軍力、中國軍力、美國國防部外文關鍵詞:Cross-strait Security、Taiwan''s Military Power、China''s Military Power、U.S. Department of Defense相關次數:

被引用:0點閱:360評分:下載:112書目收藏:0



美國國防部對臺海安全之評估，2001-2008摘要臺海安全長期以來是全球持續關註的焦點，臺海問題涉及台灣與中國對於國家主權的看法不一所致，也就是所謂的統獨爭議。在臺海安全議題上，台灣、美國、中國是三個主要行為者，其中美國在兩岸之間扮演重要的角色。軍力因素是維持臺海安全、和平與穩定的重要關鍵。由於臺海安全在相當大的程度上涉及臺海之間的軍力結構，而美國國防部對「臺海軍力評估」與「臺海安全局勢」多所著墨，本文從美國國防部的角度出發，研究其對臺海安全的評估。本文首先研究美國國防部對中國軍力進行的評估，包括對中國國防預算的看法、對中國軍事戰略與軍事能力的評估，以及解放軍對台動武的評估。接著本文研究美國國防部對台灣軍力進行的評估，包括對台灣國防預算的看法、對台灣軍事戰略與軍事能力的評估，以及台灣的防衛評估。最後，本文研究美國國防部對介入臺海危機的評估。本文研究發現，由於兩岸軍事預算差距逐漸擴大，兩岸之間的軍力已呈現失衡的局面。中國持續增強對台灣的軍力部署，其中以增進飛彈和海空封鎖能力最為明顯。台灣雖然展現一定程度的防衛決心，但台灣的國防仍有防衛限制與需要改善之處。美國則透過增強西太平洋的軍事能力，展現介入臺海危機的意願與能力，但對美國而言，最好的方式是進行預防外交，防止危機的發生。

An Evaluation on the Cross-strait Security as Performed by U.S. Department of Defense, 2001-2008AbstractCross-strait security is the global attention for a long term. Cross-strait issues usually involve different view points on national sovereignty between Taiwan and China, that is, the so-called unification or independence controversy. In cross-strait security topics, Taiwan, U.S. and China are three major actors; U.S. especially plays an important role in the cross-strait relationship. Military power factor is a key factor in keeping cross-strait security, peace and stability. Since the cross-strait security, in large extent, involves the military structure in the Taiwan strait; U.S. Department of Defense has made a lot of studies on “The military power evaluation cross the Taiwan Strait” and “The cross-strait security situation”, hence, this thesis will start from the point of view of U.S. Department of Defense to study its evaluation on the cross-strait security.In this thesis, the evaluation on China’s military power as performed by U.S. Department of Defense is studied first, it includes, for example, view on China’s budget for national defense, evaluation on China’s military strategy and military capability, and the evaluation of the military act performed by People's Liberation Army. Next in this thesis, an evaluation on Taiwan’s military power as performed by U.S. Department of Defense will be studied, which includes the view on Taiwan’s budget for national defense and an evaluation on Taiwan’s military strategy and military capability, and finally, Taiwan’s defense evaluation will be performed. Finally, an evaluation for the intervention on cross-strait crisis as evaluated by U.S. Department of Defense will be studied.It is found from this thesis that since the military budget gap across the strait gradually expands, an unbalance exists among the military power across the strait. China continues to enhance its military deployment against Taiwan, among them, the most obvious one is the enhancement of missile and sea and air blocking capability. Although Taiwan has displayed certain degree of defense determination, yet Taiwan’s national defense still has its limitation and places for improvement. However, U.S. has enhanced its military capability in West Pacific Ocean to display its willing and capability to intervene the cross-strait crisis; however, to U.S., the best way is to perform preventive diplomacy to prevent the occurrence of the crisis.

